---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const projects = [
  {
    name: "Global Metro Power Rankings",
    meta: "70,000+ parameters. 4,200+ metros. 237 countries.",
    blurb:
      "A data-driven measure of what makes a city matter globally, assembled parameter by parameter across sixteen dimensions.",
    href: "https://rankings.citizenofnowhere.org",
    cta: "Explore the rankings",
    tag: "Live",
  },
];

const notes = [
  {
    title: "On belonging to everywhere",
    date: "Coming soon",
    summary:
      "A short essay on why the insult 'citizen of nowhere' is the most interesting identity a person can hold in 2026.",
  },
  {
    title: "The fallacy of the global city index",
    date: "Coming soon",
    summary:
      "Why every major city ranking is quietly optimized for the viewpoint of a single type of reader, and what a more honest instrument would look like.",
  },
];
---

<Layout>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 md:px-10 py-16 md:py-28">
    <!-- Masthead -->
    <header class="flex items-center justify-between mb-24 md:mb-36">
      <a
        href="/"
        class="text-[11px] md:text-xs tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-[color:var(--color-accent)]"
        style="font-family: var(--font-display)"
      >
        Citizen of Nowhere
      </a>
      <nav
        class="flex items-center gap-6 md:gap-10 text-xs md:text-sm text-[color:var(--color-muted)]"
        style="font-family: var(--font-display)"
      >
        <a href="#work" class="hover:text-[color:var(--color-paper)] transition-colors">Work</a>
        <a href="#writing" class="hover:text-[color:var(--color-paper)] transition-colors">Writing</a>
        <a href="#about" class="hover:text-[color:var(--color-paper)] transition-colors">About</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="mb-28 md:mb-40">
      <p
        class="text-[11px] md:text-xs tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-[color:var(--color-accent)] mb-8"
        style="font-family: var(--font-display)"
      >
        A studio for ideas, indices, and interfaces
      </p>

      <h1
        class="text-5xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl leading-[0.95] tracking-tight font-medium mb-10"
        style="font-family: var(--font-serif)"
      >
        Cities are the unit of
        <span class="italic text-[color:var(--color-accent)]">civilization</span>.
        Countries are accidents of it.
      </h1>

      <p
        class="text-lg md:text-2xl leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-paper)]/80 max-w-2xl"
        style="font-family: var(--font-serif)"
      >
        Citizen of Nowhere is where I think out loud about metros, movement,
        measurement, and the people who belong to all places and none. Some of
        that thinking becomes writing. Some of it becomes software.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Work -->
    <section id="work" class="mb-28 md:mb-36">
      <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-10 pb-4 border-b border-[color:var(--color-line)]">
        <h2
          class="text-xs md:text-sm tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-[color:var(--color-muted)]"
          style="font-family: var(--font-display)"
        >
          Work / 001
        </h2>
        <span
          class="text-xs md:text-sm text-[color:var(--color-muted)]"
          style="font-family: var(--font-display)"
        >
          Currently live
        </span>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-12">
        {
          projects.map((p) => (
            <article class="group">
              <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-6 mb-3">
                <h3
                  class="text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-medium tracking-tight"
                  style="font-family: var(--font-serif)"
                >
                  <a
                    href={p.href}
                    class="hover:text-[color:var(--color-accent)] transition-colors"
                  >
                    {p.name}
                  </a>
                </h3>
                <span
                  class="shrink-0 text-[10px] md:text-xs tracking-[0.2em] uppercase px-2 py-1 border border-[color:var(--color-accent)] text-[color:var(--color-accent)]"
                  style="font-family: var(--font-display)"
                >
                  {p.tag}
                </span>
              </div>
              <p
                class="text-xs md:text-sm tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-[color:var(--color-muted)] mb-5"
                style="font-family: var(--font-display)"
              >
                {p.meta}
              </p>
              <p
                class="text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-paper)]/75 max-w-2xl mb-6"
                style="font-family: var(--font-serif)"
              >
                {p.blurb}
              </p>
              <a
                href={p.href}
                class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm md:text-base text-[color:var(--color-accent)] hover:text-[color:var(--color-paper)] transition-colors"
                style="font-family: var(--font-display)"
              >
                {p.cta}
                <span aria-hidden="true">-&gt;</span>
              </a>
            </article>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Writing -->
    <section id="writing" class="mb-28 md:mb-36">
      <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-10 pb-4 border-b border-[color:var(--color-line)]">
        <h2
          class="text-xs md:text-sm tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-[color:var(--color-muted)]"
          style="font-family: var(--font-display)"
        >
          Writing
        </h2>
        <span
          class="text-xs md:text-sm text-[color:var(--color-muted)]"
          style="font-family: var(--font-display)"
        >
          Notes, essays, field reports
        </span>
      </div>

      <ul class="divide-y divide-[color:var(--color-line)]">
        {
          notes.map((n) => (
            <li class="py-6 flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-baseline md:justify-between gap-2 md:gap-10">
              <div class="max-w-2xl">
                <h3
                  class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-medium mb-2"
                  style="font-family: var(--font-serif)"
                >
                  {n.title}
                </h3>
                <p
                  class="text-sm md:text-base text-[color:var(--color-paper)]/70"
                  style="font-family: var(--font-serif)"
                >
                  {n.summary}
                </p>
              </div>
              <span
                class="shrink-0 text-xs tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[color:var(--color-muted)]"
                style="font-family: var(--font-display)"
              >
                {n.date}
              </span>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- About -->
    <section id="about" class="mb-28 md:mb-36">
      <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-10 pb-4 border-b border-[color:var(--color-line)]">
        <h2
          class="text-xs md:text-sm tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-[color:var(--color-muted)]"
          style="font-family: var(--font-display)"
        >
          About
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6 max-w-2xl text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-paper)]/80" style="font-family: var(--font-serif)">
        <p>
          The phrase was meant as an insult. It was delivered from a podium, in
          a political speech, to describe people who considered themselves
          citizens of the world. The implication was that a person who belongs
          to everywhere belongs to nowhere, and therefore, to nothing.
        </p>
        <p>
          I took the label and kept it, because I think the opposite is true.
          Someone who has lived in more than one country, who has worked across
          more than one language, who has built things for people who do not
          look like them, is not stateless in any diminished sense. They are
          simply loyal to the city and the idea rather than the flag.
        </p>
        <p>
          This site is where I publish the work that follows from that
          orientation. Indices that take metros seriously as the organising
          unit of modern life. Essays on movement, measurement, and belonging.
          Software that makes it easier to see the world as it actually is,
          rather than as national summaries want you to see it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer class="pt-10 border-t border-[color:var(--color-line)]">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between gap-4 text-xs md:text-sm text-[color:var(--color-muted)]" style="font-family: var(--font-display)">
        <span>&copy; {new Date().getFullYear()} Citizen of Nowhere</span>
        <span>citizenofnowhere.org</span>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </main>
</Layout>
